This paper discusses the forensic analysis of internet browsers, specifically focusing on the privacy-preserving features of these browsers. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR), as it deals with investigating cybercrimes and the use of private browsing features to conceal illegal online activity. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple tools and forensic approaches, which could also fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), software engineering (cs.SE), and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
